N2  - Persons living with human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection (PLWH)
have accentuated risks for age-associated comorbidities. Compared with
the general population, PLWH have a twofold higher risk of
cardiovascular disease, a threefold increased risk of fracture, and a
